arts.ttl: Toppmöller full of praise for his team after Wolfsburg draw
arts.sum: Dino Toppmöller believed his team deserved more than a draw after Eintracht Frankfurt’s combative performance against VfL Wolfsburg.

arts.ttl: Can Uzun header rescues point for Eintracht Frankfurt against Wolfsburg
arts.sum: Substitute Can Uzun's late header cancelled out a Tuta own-goal as Eintracht Frankfurt and Wolfsburg battled to a share of the spoils in a game that burst into life after the break at Deutsche Bank Park. The match took another turn when Wolfsburg were forced to change goalkeepers in the 66th minute, with Marius Müller making his Bundesliga debut replacing the injured Grabara.

arts.ttl: Frankfurt and Wolfsburg shared spoils in a lively encounter
arts.sum: Eintracht Frankfurt fought back to a home draw against VfL Wolfsburg in Sunday’s early Bundesliga fixture.

arts.ttl: Official | Eintracht Frankfurt purchase Arthur Theate for €19m including bonuses
arts.sum: Eintracht Frankfurt's permanent capture of defender Arthur Theate has been officially confirmed.

arts.ttl: Arthur Theate pens long-term Eagles deal
arts.sum: Eintracht Frankfurt have made the Belgian defender’s loan move from Stade Rennais FC permanent, with Theate signing a contract until 30 June 2029.

arts.ttl: Eintracht Frankfurt to sign Arthur Theate on permanent basis from Rennes
arts.sum: Florian Plettenberg reports that Eintracht Frankfurt will sign Belgian defender Arthur Theate from Rennes on a permanent basis for a base fee of €13m plus a further €6m in bonuses.…

arts.ttl: Omar Marmoush rides the rhythm to set the tempo for Guardiola’s new beat
arts.sum: The Egyptian adds another gear to Manchester City’s shift to more direct play with a short-passing game as backup Everything is new. Everything is different. Omar Marmoush steps off the plane at Manchester Airport and what greets him is a kind of sensory overload. He peers through blacked-out windows of his chauffeured car at the city he now calls home. “What are the names of the supermarkets?” he asks. “Tesco,” comes the reply. “Asda. Sainsbury’s. Aldi.” On the pitch, it’s a similar story. “He has something special,” Erling Haaland confirms after a dynamic debut against Chelsea last Saturday night. “He’s going to be a fantastic player for us. It’s about getting to know him as soon as possible, because there are so many important games coming.” Continue reading...

arts.ttl: Transfer news and rumours: Kelechi Iheanacho to Celtic, Patrick Wimmer to Leicester City, Marcus Edwards to Burnley
arts.sum: Sports Mole rounds up the latest transfer news and rumours, including Kelechi Iheanacho to Celtic, Patrick Wimmer to Leicester City and Marcus Edwards to Burnley.

arts.ttl: Eintracht Frankfurt vs. Wolfsburg preview: Die Adler looking to extend unbeaten run
arts.sum: Eintracht Frankfurt will look to extend their four-game unbeaten league run when they welcome Wolfsburg to Deutsche Bank Arena for Sunday’s Bundesliga fixture.

arts.ttl: Why Man City believe Omar Marmoush is the heir to Mohamed Salah's throne... and how Erling Haaland is set to benefit most from Pep Guardiola's new £63m man
arts.sum: JACK GAUGHAN: Less than three hours before Wednesday's victory over Club Brugge, Omar Marmoush was standing on the indoor pitch at Manchester City 's training ground.
